Timothy Leary's Last Trip - 1997 [dvdrip]

This behind-the-scenes look at Dr. Timothy Leary, pioneer in psychology and consciousness-raising of the 1960s, documents the life of the man who led a 30-year struggle to have the youth of the times &quot;Tune In, Turn On, Drop Out&quot;. Timothy Leary's Last Trip follows Leary from his first days at West Point Military Academy to his final trip in cyber-space. Diagnosed with terminal cancer in 1995, Leary chose to exit this planet with all the energy of his countless excursions into the outer realms of the mind.  Joining Leary on his final trip are Ken Kesey and the Merry Pranksters (The Electric Kool-Aid Acid Test), the legendary troupe of 60s counter-culture jesters, who reunite with the high priest of LSD for one last psychedelic blow-out at Wavy Gravy's &quot;Hog Farm Picnic&quot;. (This event took place two weeks after the death of Jerry Garcia, so the documentary contains a bit of a tribute to Jerry.)
Includes music by the Grateful Dead, featuring Turn On Your Love Light, I Know You Rider, Bertha, Goin' Down the Road Feeling Bad, He's Gone, King Solomon's Mines, and Cold Rain and Snow.
